            "type": "h1",
            "text": "Design Patterns"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Design patterns are reusable solutions to common software design problems. They provide a template for how to solve a problem that can be used in many different situations. This page explores various design patterns, their implementations across different programming languages, and modern variants that leverage contemporary language features."
        },
        {
            "type": "blocks",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "id": "creational_patterns",
                    "title": "Creational patterns",
                    "style": "text_style",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "blocks",
                            "blocks": [
                                {
                                    "id": "abstract_factory",
                                    "title": "Abstract Factory",
                                    "content": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "text",
                                            "text": "Create families of related objects without specifying concrete classes. Shown as classic factory-method-based examples."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "text",
                                            "text": "Example implementation across language variants."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "code",
                                            "path": "design_patterns/abstract_factory"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
