                                    "id": "singleton",
                                    "title": "Singleton",
                                    "content": [
                                        {
                                            "type": "text",
                                            "text": "Ensure a class has only one instance and provide a global point of access."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "note",
                                            "text": "Note: Singleton is often considered an anti-pattern in modern software design due to issues with testability and global state, but it's included here for completeness."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "text",
                                            "text": "Example implementation across language variants."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "type": "code",
                                            "path": "design_patterns/singleton"
                                        }
